<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-03-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-03-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="1205" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1205">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/211.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Consul <persName type="to">Hostetter</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of Stater</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-16">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 16, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Consul, Mazatlan, reports that Constitutionalist authorities are
                            collecting from American mining companies back taxes which have already
                            been paid to central administration.</p>
                        <p>Bring to attention of appropriate authorities with protest against
                            collection these taxes a second time, and state that under principles of
                            international law these companies should be relieved of all further
                            obligation with regard to taxes already paid by them to central
                            administration.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>